('36817', '1', 'b'Cook couscous in well-salted boiling water, uncovered, until tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in sugar snaps 3 minutes before couscous is done.''),
('36817', '2', 'b'Drain and transfer to a bowl, then stir in 1/2 tablespoon butter and salt and pepper to taste.''),
('36817', '3', 'b'While couscous and sugar snaps cook, toss shrimp with 1/8 teaspoon each of salt and pepper.''),
('36817', '4', 'b'Heat remaining tablespoon butter in a 10-inch heavy skillet over medium-high heat until foam subsides. Saut\xc3\xa9 shrimp, turning once, until just cooked through, about 3 minutes total.''),
('36817', '5', 'b'Transfer shrimp with a slotted spoon to a plate.''),
('36817', '6', 'b'Add wine, tomato, and sugar to skillet and boil until tomato starts to fall apart, about 4 minutes. Return shrimp to skillet and stir in tarragon.''),
('36817', '7', 'b'Season with salt and pepper.''),
('36817', '8', 'b'Serve shrimp and pan sauce on top of pearl couscous.''),
('36818', '1', 'b'Cook noodles in large saucepan ofboiling salted water until tender, stirringoccasionally, 4 to 5 minutes.''),
('36818', '2', 'b'Drain. Rinsewith cold water. drain well. Using scissors,cut noodles into thirds.''),
('36818', '3', 'b'Whisk lime juice, fish sauce, chili-garlicsauce, and sugar in small bowl until sugardissolves.''),
('36818', '4', 'b'Place shrimp in medium bowl.''),
('36818', '5', 'b'Add 2 tablespoons dressing. toss to coat.''),
('36818', '6', 'b'Divide noodles among bowls. Topwith cucumber slices and all remainingingredients. Spoon shrimp with dressingover, and drizzle with remaining dressing.''),
('36818', '7', 'b'Bon App\xc3\xa9tit''),
('36821', '1', 'b'Combine all dressing ingredients with 1/4 cup water in a blender. set aside. Coat a large skillet or wok with cooking spray. heat over high heat and add 1 1/2 teaspoons oil. When oil is hot, cook tofu and scallions 1 minute, then turn tofu once. cook 1 to 2 minutes more.''),
('36821', '2', 'b'Transfer tofu to a cutting board, cut into 1/2-inch cubes and place in a bowl with scallions.''),
('36821', '3', 'b'Add remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil to skillet. Stir in broccoli, edamame and mushrooms. Reduce heat to medium. cook, stirring often, 3 to 4 minutes.''),
('36821', '4', 'b'Add broth. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, 3 to 4 minutes.''),
('36821', '5', 'b'Remove from heat and stir in peas, salt and pepper.''),
('36821', '6', 'b'Add noodles and vegetable mixture to tofu mixture. Toss with dressing to coat.''),
('36821', '7', 'b'Self''),
('36828', '1', 'b'Whisk first 5 ingredients in medium bowl to blend.''),
('36828', '2', 'b'Add tofu and stir to coat. let marinate 30 minutes.''),
('36828', '3', 'b'Drain, reserving marinade in small bowl.''),
('36828', '4', 'b'Whisk 1/4 cup water and cornstarch into marinade.''),
('36828', '5', 'b'Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.''),
('36828', '6', 'b'Add tofu and saut\xc3\xa9 until golden, about 2 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer tofu to plate.''),
('36828', '7', 'b'Add remaining 1 tablespoon vegetable oil to skillet.''),
('36828', '8', 'b'Add mushrooms and stir-fry until tender, about 3 minutes.''),
('36828', '9', 'b'Add sugar snap peas. stir-fry 2 minutes.''),
('36828', '10', 'b'Add garlic and ginger. stir-fry 30 seconds. Return tofu to skillet. drizzle reserved marinade mixture over. Stir-fry until marinade thickens slightly, about 30 seconds. Season to taste with salt and pepper.''),
('36828', '11', 'b'Transfer to bowl. Sprinkle with green onions and serve.''),
('36828', '12', 'b'Per serving: calories, 195. total fat, 11 g. saturated fat, 1 g. cholesterol, 0. fiber, 3 g''),
('36828', '13', 'b'Bon App\xc3\xa9tit''),
('36829', '1', 'b'In a small bowl, whisk the lemon juice with the olive oil, chervil and honey and season with salt and pepper.''),
('36829', '2', 'b'Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to a boil.''),
('36829', '3', 'b'Add the asparagus and carrots and cook until the asparagus is bright green and the carrots are barely tender, about 2 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the asparagus and carrots to a platter.''),
('36829', '4', 'b'Add the sugar snap peas to the saucepan and cook until they turn bright green, about 30 seconds. transfer to the platter.''),
('36829', '5', 'b'Cut the sugar snap peas into julienne strips. Halve the asparagus stalks lengthwise, then halve the asparagus pieces crosswise.''),
('36829', '6', 'b'In a large bowl, toss the lettuce, asparagus, carrots, sugar snap peas, radishes, mushrooms, fennel, cucumber, avocado, sprouts and cashews.''),
('36829', '7', 'b'Add the vinaigrette and toss well.''),
('36829', '8', 'b'Serve right away.''),
('36832', '1', 'b'In a blender, puree the tomato with the vinegar, mustard and garlic. With the blender on, slowly pour in the olive oil until smooth. Scrape the sauce into a bowl. Stir in the chopped anchovies, olives and capers and season the puttanesca with salt and pepper.''),
('36832', '2', 'b'In a medium saucepan of boiling salted water, blanch the sugar snaps until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.''),
('36832', '3', 'b'Drain and refresh in cold water. Reserve the blanching water.''),
('36832', '4', 'b'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.''),
('36832', '5', 'b'Add the garlic and shallot and cook over low heat until softened, about 2 minutes.''),
('36832', '6', 'b'Add the tomato and sugar snaps and cook, stirring, for 3 minutes.''),
('36832', '7', 'b'Add the thyme and capers and season with salt and pepper.''),
('36832', '8', 'b'Remove from the heat.''),
('36832', '9', 'b'Preheat the oven to 30''),
('36832', '10', 'b'Bring the sugar snap blanching water back to a boil.''),
('36832', '11', 'b'Add the fennel quarters and cook until tender, about 8 minutes.''),
('36832', '12', 'b'Drain and let cool. Pat dry with paper towels.''),
('36832', '13', 'b'Put the flour in a shallow bowl and season generously with salt and pepper. Crack the eggs into another shallow bowl and beat them with the milk. In a medium saucepan, heat 1 inch of vegetable oil to 35''),
('36832', '14', 'b'Dredge the fennel in the flour, then dip the wedges in the beaten eggs and dredge again in the flour. Working in 2 batches, fry the fennel, turning once, until golden brown, about 3 minutes.''),
('36832', '15', 'b'Transfer the fennel to a rack set over a rimmed baking sheet and keep warm in the oven.''),
('36832', '16', 'b'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan. Rub the tuna steaks with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill over high heat until deeply browned outside and rare in the center, about 3 minutes per side.''),
('36832', '17', 'b'Transfer the tuna to a cutting board and cut each steak into 1/3-inch-thick slices.''),
('36832', '18', 'b'Reheat the sugar snaps and spoon them onto plates. Lay the sliced tuna on the plates and drizzle the puttanesca sauce around the fish. Set 2 fennel fritters on each plate, garnish with the whole anchovies and serve at once.''),
('36839', '1', 'b'Cook rice according to package directions.Cover to keep warm. set aside.''),
('36839', '2', 'b'Meanwhile, whisk juice, soy sauce, andcornstarch in medium bowl until cornstarchdissolves.''),
('36839', '3', 'b'Mix in orange peel.''),
('36839', '4', 'b'Heat oil in large wok or nonstick skilletover high heat.''),
('36839', '5', 'b'Add onion and crushed redpepper. Stir-fry 30 seconds. Sprinkle chickenwith salt and pepper.''),
('36839', '6', 'b'Add to wok and stir-fryuntil onion is crisp-tender and chicken is justcooked through, about 4 minutes.''),
('36839', '7', 'b'Add sugarsnap peas and juice mixture. Toss untilsauce thickens and comes to boil and peasare crisp-tender, about 2 minutes. Seasonwith salt and pepper.''),
('36839', '8', 'b'Serve with rice.''),
('36847', '1', 'b'Place carrots and shallots in a pan. cover with water. Bring to boil. cook until tender, 7 minutes.''),
('36847', '2', 'b'Drain.''),
('36847', '3', 'b'Preheat oven to 425F. In a large bowl toss carrots, shallots, fennel and garlic cloves with 2 Tbsp. olive oil, 1 Tbsp. chopped garlic, 1 Tbsp. tarragon, salt and pepper.''),
('36847', '4', 'b'Spread in a single layer on a baking sheet. Roast for 15 minutes, stirring once.''),
('36847', '5', 'b'Toss remaining vegetables with remaining olive oil and garlic, 1 Tbsp. tarragon, salt and pepper.''),
('36847', '6', 'b'Place on a baking sheet in a single layer and roast on separate oven rack for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Toss all vegetables together, sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. tarragon and serve.''),
('36849', '1', 'b'Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil over medium-high heat.''),
('36849', '2', 'b'Add the pasta, and cook until al dente, 8 to 10 minutes.''),
('36849', '3', 'b'Drain, cover pot, and set aside.''),
('36849', '4', 'b'Stir the cream cheese, Gorgonzola cheese, and cream together in a bowl until smooth. Set aside.''),
('36849', '5', 'b'Bring another large pot of lightly salted water to a boil over medium-high heat.''),
('36849', '6', 'b'Add the sugar snap peas, and cook until crisp, 1 to 2 minutes.''),
('36849', '7', 'b'Drain. Toss peas with butter. Stir cream cheese mixture into peas, and toss to coat evenly.''),
('36849', '8', 'b'Serve immediately over cooked pasta.''),
('36850', '1', 'b'In a 4-quart saucepan cover potatoes with salted cold water by 1 inch and simmer 10 minutes, or until potatoes are tender when pierced with a sharp knife.''),
('36850', '2', 'b'Drain potatoes in a colander. Potatoes may be cooked 1 day ahead and cooled before being chilled in a sealable plastic bag. Bring potatoes to room temperature before proceeding.''),
('36850', '3', 'b'Shell peas if using fresh and trim sugar snap peas. In a large skillet heat oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking and saut\xc3\xa9 all vegetables, stirring frequently, until sugar snaps are crisp-tender and potatoes are heated through, about 4 minutes. Season vegetables with salt and pepper.''),
('36856', '1', 'b'Cook onions in oil in a wide 6-quart heavy pot over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, 5 to 7 minutes.''),
('36856', '2', 'b'Add sugar snaps and cook, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender and bright green, 6 to 8 minutes.''),
('36856', '3', 'b'Add sugar and cook, stirring, 1 minute.''),
('36856', '4', 'b'Pur\xc3\xa9e pea mixture with 6 cups water in a blender in 6 batches until very smooth, about 30 seconds per batch, then pour through a very fine sieve, discarding solids (do not press on solids). Stir in salt and chill broth, covered, until very cold, about 8 hours. (Do not chill longer or soup will discolor.)''),
('36856', '5', 'b'Whisk together sour cream, zest, and remaining 2 1/2 tablespoons water in a small bowl, then pour through a very fine sieve into another small bowl (to remove air bubbles).''),
('36856', '6', 'b'Serve broth topped with lemon cream.''),
('36860', '1', 'b'Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.''),
('36860', '2', 'b'Add mushrooms, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and pepper. saut 3 minutes.''),
('36860', '3', 'b'Add garlic, and saut 1 minute.''),
('36860', '4', 'b'Add wine, and reduce liquid by half, cooking about 8 minutes.''),
('36860', '5', 'b'Add cream and, if desired, nutmeg. simmer 2 minutes.''),
('36860', '6', 'b'Remove sauce from heat, and stir in cheese. Set aside.''),
('36860', '7', 'b'Add 1 1/2 tablespoons salt to a large pot of water, and bring to a boil.''),
('36860', '8', 'b'Add pasta, and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until al dente.''),
('36860', '9', 'b'Add broccoli and asparagus, and cook 2 minutes.''),
('36860', '10', 'b'Add sugar snap peas, and cook 1 minute or until vegetables are crisp-tender.''),
('36860', '11', 'b'Drain, reserving 1/4 cup water.''),
('36860', '12', 'b'Transfer to a separate skillet. Stir in tomato halves and fresh herbs, and gently toss pasta with sauce, adding reserved water as needed for moisture.''),
('36860', '13', 'b'Garnish, if desired.''),
('36862', '1', 'b'Stir together salsa and sour cream. Scrape the dip you made into a small bowl.''),
('36862', '2', 'b'Put the small bowl in the middle of a big plate. Arrange the veggies all around the dip and serve.''),
('36864', '1', 'b'Heat a wok or large skillet over high heat.''),
('36864', '2', 'b'Add 2 tablespoons of the oil and heat for 30 seconds.''),
('36864', '3', 'b'Add the steak and stir-fry until cooked through, 3 to 4 minutes.''),
('36864', '4', 'b'Transfer to a plate. Wipe out the pan. Reduce heat to medium-high, add the remaining oil, and heat for 30 seconds.''),
('36864', '5', 'b'Add the bell pepper and cook, stirring constantly, for 10 seconds.''),
('36864', '6', 'b'Add the sweet potato and water. Cover partially and cook, stirring occasionally, for 7 minutes.''),
('36864', '7', 'b'Add the peas and scallions and cook for 1 minute.''),
('36864', '8', 'b'Add the Garlicky Hoisin Sauce and increase heat to high. When it starts to bubble, add the steak. Stir-fry until warmed through, about 1 minute.''),
('36864', '9', 'b'Serve immediately over the rice. Tip: Pork or turkey cutlets can stand in for the beef, and green beans for the sugar snaps.''),
('36870', '1', 'b'Cook the rice according to package directions, omitting salt and fat. Stir in 1/3 cup chopped green onions, chopped dry-roasted cashews, and salt. set aside, and keep warm.''),
('36870', '2', 'b'Combine 2/3 cup chicken broth, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 2 tablespoons low-sodium soy sauce, and honey in a small bowl, and set aside.''),
('36870', '3', 'b'Combine pork, remaining 1 tablespoon cornstarch, and the remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce in a bowl, tossing well to coat.''),
('36870', '4', 'b'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.''),
('36870', '5', 'b'Add pork. saut 4 minutes or until browned.''),
('36870', '6', 'b'Remove from pan.''),
('36870', '7', 'b'Add remaining 1 teaspoon oil to pan.''),
('36870', '8', 'b'Add mushrooms and 1 cup onion. saut 2 minutes. Stir in ginger and garlic. saut 30 seconds.''),
('36870', '9', 'b'Add peas and bell pepper to pan. saut 1 minute. Stir in pork. saut 1 minute.''),
('36870', '10', 'b'Add reserved broth mixture to pan. Bring to a boil. cook 1 minute or until thick, stirring constantly.''),
('36870', '11', 'b'Serve over cashew rice.''),
('36874', '1', 'b'Whisk together all dressing ingredients in a large bowl and let stand at room temperature while making salad.''),
('36877', '1', 'b'Coat a stove-top grill pan or griddle with cooking spray and set over medium-high heat to preheat.''),
('36877', '2', 'b'In a shallow dish, whisk together soy sauce, honey, molasses, ginger, garlic, liquid smoke seasoning, and black pepper.''),
('36877', '3', 'b'Add chicken strips and turn to coat.''),
('36877', '4', 'b'Place chicken on hot grill and cook 5 to 7 minutes, until cooked through, turning once during cooking.''),
('36877', '5', 'b'Remove chicken from grill pan and roll in toasted sesame seeds.''),
